title: For Sale:  Flare Pistol Outfit - Polish M78, 26.5mm
postcontent:
This is a Polish Model 78 flare pistol that fires 26.5mm flare & smoke rounds. The M78 was made by Radom Arsenal as evidenced by the Circle 11 stamp on top of the barrel. It is a licensed copy of the HK P2A1. 

I've laid this pistol next to a P2A1 that I own and they appear identical except for the stampings on the frame and barrel. Although I haven't tried it appears that many if not all parts would interchange.

I can only describe this pistol as excellent with 98%+ of it's original finish. Mechanical function is perfect and bore looks new. I don't think that this particular pistol has been fired.

 It comes with a  green rope lanyard, a military flap style holster with shoulder strap that is in very good shape which is made of a a weatherproof woven vinyl in an OD green color. The holster has room for the pistol, a supply of flare cartridges and miscellaneous items.

Also included is an adapter that allows you to fire any .22LR, Long or Short ammunition turning this pistol into an excellent emergency self defense/survival tool for your "bug out" bag. Plus there is another adapter for firing the less expensive 12 gauge flares that are commonly available.

Finally there is a complete cleaning kit that has a stiff nylon brush for normal cleaning. A brass bristle brush for really heavy duty cleaning and a felt tipped rod that fits the bore snuggly eliminating the need for cleaning patches.

$225.00 with pickup in the Brandon area, or I can ship to places where this is legal for $15.
I will not ship to NY, CT, CA, HI, AK or IL without a current FOID card. Buyer must be at least 21 (because of .22 adapter) and I will check.

Thanks for looking

title: For Trade:  SIG SAUER P220 45ACP
postcontent:
I am retired Navy and carried the 1911, Glock, and Browning Hi Power while on active duty. I've discovered I'm just not a DA/SA decocker kind of guy.

I had assumed it was a stainless model, however, after speaking to the Custom Shop Director and Senior Gunsmith at SIG SAUER learned it is in fact a low-glare nickel variant of which very few were ever produced. As you can see it does not have the contrasting controls as the models produced today, instead it is all nickel.

It is super clean, functionally flawless, and remarkably accurate. No stains, scratches, or blemishes of any kind. If it is not a rare piece, it is certainly hard to find. Zero defects. Comes with hard plastic carry case and three factory mags.

title: For Sale/Trade:  1000 rnd. sealed can, ALL STEEL CORE 5.56 ammo, Carl Gustaf, M855
postcontent:
This ammo is a bit different than the soon to be banned M855 SS109.  The SS109 bullet has a hardened steel penetrator and a mostly lead core.  This Swedish ammo has a 62gr. bullet with a hardened steel penetrator at the tip and a mild steel core - ALL STEEL core.  No lead at all, hence the "non-toxic" designation.  I guess it's a bit like the M855A1 ammo.

The unique bullet used in this ammo is longer than the green tipped SS109 and is very similar in length to the 77 Sierra Match king bullets (see photo - MK left, Carl Gustaff center, SS109 right).  It's supposed to provide 2MOA or better accuracy and also outperforms the M855 in penetration performance.  

The ammo comes in a sealed .50cal storage can and is packaged on stripper clips.  Each can comes with two mag loaders inside, too!
